The paper deals with the problem of constructing minimum cost and minimum edge $xy-$monotone spanning geometric graphs, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of graphs and their properties, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of optimization techniques and approximation algorithms indicates that it could be relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as well. Finally, the paper involves the study of geometric graphs and their properties, which could make it relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
